

⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 105/120 – Adaptive Query Execution (AQE)

🎤 Interview Question

Your Spark job is slow because partition sizes vary significantly, and Spark chooses a suboptimal join strategy.

How can AQE help?


---

✅ Recommended Solution

Enable AQE:

spark.conf.set(
    "spark.sql.adaptive.enabled",
    "true"
)


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is AQE?

Answer

Adaptive Query Execution optimizes the execution plan during runtime based on actual data statistics.


---

Q2. What can AQE optimize?

Answer

Join strategy

Shuffle partitions

Skewed partitions



---

Q3. Why is AQE useful?

Answer

It improves performance automatically without changing application code.


---

⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 106/120 – Shuffle Optimization

🎤 Interview Question

A groupBy() operation is taking a long time because it triggers a large shuffle.

How can you reduce shuffle overhead?


---

✅ Recommended Solution

Example:

spark.conf.set(
    "spark.sql.shuffle.partitions",
    "200"
)

df.groupBy("department").count().show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. What is a shuffle?

Answer

A shuffle redistributes data across executors so related records are grouped together.


---

Q2. Which operations trigger shuffles?

Answer

groupBy()

join()

distinct()

orderBy()

repartition()



---

Q3. Why are shuffles expensive?

Answer

They involve network I/O, disk I/O, and data serialization, making them one of the costliest Spark operations.


